cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "The n=4 Lonely Runner spectrum near 1/4: delta_2(4)=3/14 and a candidate exceptional element D=2/7"
authors:
  - family-names: Bonfioli
    given-names: Vico
license: Apache-2.0
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20534835
abstract: "Two elementary finite-calculation results on the n=4 view-obstruction / Lonely Runner D-spectrum near its first accumulation point 1/4, in the framework of Jain-Kravitz (arXiv:2411.12684): (A) no saturated 2-dimensional subtorus of (R/Z)^4 has D-value in the open interval (3/14, 1/4), i.e. delta_2(4)=3/14, proved by a Hermite-normal-form reduction and a 3-runner doubling cascade with an exact finite verification; (B) the observation that D=2/7 appears to be an exceptional element of S_1(4) cap (1/4,1/2] (the finite symmetric difference of Jain-Kravitz Theorem 1.3). Developed with assistance from Anthropic's Claude; all arithmetic is elementary and reproducible."
keywords:
  - Lonely Runner Conjecture
  - view-obstruction
  - relative spectra
  - number theory
